        public static java.awt.Font getDefaultPropertyFont()
        returns the default font that will most likely be assigned to property editors during their creation and initialization phase.

        WARNING: This font accessor is intended for initialization purposes only and may not be the font assigned to any given editor during initialization.

      • stopEditing

        public boolean stopEditing()
        Retrieves the current value in this property panel's editor and sets it in its PropertySet.

        This is intended for use in situations where the editor's current value should be stored when the panel is being refreshed, changing targets, closing, etc.

        Returns:
        true if the PropertySet accepted the value and will handle notifying listeners of the changes; false otherwise
